sql:
SELECT a.age_group, a.gender, COUNT(a.movie_id) AS movie_count, AVG(a.rating) AS average_rating
FROM audience a
GROUP BY a.age_group, a.gender;

external_knowledge:
- Average rating >= 7.0 indicates a well-received film by the audience; 
- "Audience appreciation scores" refer to the average ratings given by viewers, typically on a scale like 1-10; 
- "Opening weekend takings" refer to the total revenue earned during the first weekend of a film's release; 
- "Domestic earnings" are box office sales within the film's home country; 
- "International earnings" are sales from audiences outside the home country; 
- "Global earnings" represent total revenue from both domestic and international markets.
